# Modern CLI Tools

Always prefer these faster, modern alternatives when running shell commands:

| Instead of | Use | Example |
|------------|-----|---------|
| `grep` | `rg` (ripgrep) | `rg "pattern" .` |
| `find` | `fd` | `fd "*.py"` |
| `cat` | `bat` | `bat file.py` |
| `sed` | `sd` | `sd 'old' 'new' file.txt` |
| `diff` | `delta` | `git diff \| delta` |
| `jq` | `jaq` | `jaq '.key' file.json` |
| `ps` | `procs` | `procs` |
| 'node:*' | 'bun' | `bun run index.ts` |

## Quick Examples

```bash
# ❌ BAD
grep -r "TODO" .
find . -name "*.ts"
cat src/main.py

# ✅ GOOD
rg "TODO"
fd -e ts
bat src/main.py
```
